22. opportunitates: the word opportunitas is ‘opportuneness’ rather than ‘opportunity’. To say that friendship has ‘opportune- nesses’ is equivalent to saying that it shows the characteristic of ‘opportuneness' on many occasions. Cicero uses the plural of ab straet nouns like this more frequently than any other author. Cf.
